This paper proposes a method for automatically discovering efficient representations for reinforcement learning problems. The paper discusses kernel-based RL, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves searching over a space of kernel structures, which can be seen as a form of optimization or search (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of dynamic programming algorithms for solving MDPs, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions evaluating the method on a synthetic problem, which suggests the use of robotics or control applications (cs.RO).
